Program for finding the maximum recorded temprature for year 2015 from NCDC weather records.

I/P : Raw NCDC data. 
     Consider input as text input format.
 
Map : Data Preparation phase. It drop the bad records: filter out temp that are missing, suspect or erroneous.

Reduce : Find out the maximum temp from all data provided by map function.

O/P : Maximum global temprature recorded in year 2015.

DataSet : you can download dataset from NCDC, http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/ for any year.

Compile and Run:
1) create a jar file.
2) put your dataset in hdfs
3) run a jar. 
 
